[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    196[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe specifies API Gateway with WAF integration but does not address per-caller rate limiting. A buggy portal page that calls the recommender in a loop (a common bug: re-render triggers re-fetch triggers re-render) can blow through Bedrock's per-account TPS quota for the embedding model, which would degrade the service for every other patient. WAF can rate-limit on IP or header values, but the more useful axis here is per-[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mpatient_id[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m rate limiting, which WAF can do with a custom rule on a request header.[K
