[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    213[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mFix:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m Two small improvements. First, clamp the cumulative score to a reasonable range (e.g., [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mmin(2.0, max(0.05, score))[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m). Second, log each multiplicative factor that fired so the explanation feature shows the audit trail per item, not just a final score. Both are one-line additions to the pseudocode and meaningfully improve auditability without changing the model's behavior in the common case.[K
