[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    260[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The recipe says "API Gateway gives you a single authenticated endpoint" but does not say whether the API Gateway is regional/public or private (VPC endpoint exposed via interface endpoint). For the patient portal, public is appropriate (the portal lives outside the VPC). For service-to-service calls from the email-composer Lambda or the post-visit summary generator, private is preferable: keeps the entire request path inside AWS networking, avoids unnecessary public DNS resolution, and makes WAF rules simpler.[K
