[0m[48;2;40;67;43m[39m+    271[0m:[39m[48;2;24;38;30m [38;2;191;97;106m-[38;2;191;97;106m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mProblem:[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;191;97;106m The content CMS is typically external to the VPC (a SaaS product, an on-prem CMS reachable via VPN or Direct Connect, or a separate AWS account). The pseudocode pulls content via [38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;163;190;140mCMS.GetContent(content_event.content_id, content_event.version)[38;2;163;190;140m`[38;2;191;97;106m. This necessarily egresses the VPC. The recipe is silent on the egress controls for that path: NAT through a controlled allow-list, VPN/Direct Connect for on-prem CMS, IAM-signed cross-account API for AWS-hosted CMS.[K
