[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    13[0m:[38;5;10m[49m The opening Maria-with-the-A1c-of-8.2-then-9.4-then-9.1-then-8.8 vignette earns its position as the chapter's strongest single articulation of the patient-quietly-failing-the-implicit-homework-assignment failure mode, with the salad spinner and the Tuesday macaroni-and-cheese and the metformin-stomach-pains-nobody-warned-her-about as recipe-distinct grounding details. The "she did not know what an A1c was" framing, the "the doctor was kind about it but also visibly disappointed in a way Maria did not need to have explained to her" passage, and the "the thing Maria would have wanted, if she had been able to articulate it, was a person to talk to" pivot into the broad-middle-not-high-risk-enough-for-care-management framing are the recipe's strongest single passage on the eighty-nine-days-twenty-three-hours-and-forty-one-minutes-between-visits primitive. The "what changed, around 2023, is that conversational AI got good enough to make the in-between-visits engagement feel like a relationship rather than a tracking interface" pivot earns its position as the recipe's clearest articulation of the relationship-quality-as-product primitive.
