d to in-body content. MEDIUM — strengthen patient_id-cross-check in every tool Lambda against the verified session token (defense-in-depth beyond Agent-level scoping) and document this in the tool contract. MEDIUM — segregate mandatory-reporting disclosure store with separate KMS key, narrower IAM scope, and break-glass access logging distinct from routine care-team alerts. MEDIUM — voice-channel recording retention, redaction of PHI from recordings/transcripts, and BAA scope for Connect/Lex should be called out alongside the existing chat audit story. LOW — 988/911 routing is US-specific; flag international-deployment crisis-routing as out-of-scope or add a per-region crisis-routing table. The draft already flags many of these via inline TODO comments (S1-S7, A1-A11, N1) with named owners and concrete scope, which constitutes adequate prioritized remediation; the additional findings above should be folded into the existing TODO set or in-body content before production sign-off. Recipe meets the bar for an expert-reviewed draft with the noted prioritized findings."}